}\r\n};\r\n\r\ninterface OpenAIContentPart {\r\n  type: \"text\" | \"image_url\";\r\n  text?: string;\r\n  image_url?: { url: string };\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface OpenAIChatMessage {\r\n  role: \"system\" | \"user\" | \"assistant\";\r\n  content: string | OpenAIContentPart[];\r\n}\r\n\r\ninterface OpenAIRequest {\r\n  messages: OpenAIChatMessage[];\r\n  model: string;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction mapMessagesToGemini(messages: OpenAIChatMessage[]): Content[] {\r\n  const geminiContents: Content[] = [];\r\n\r\n  for (const msg of messages) {\r\n    if (msg.role === \"system\") continue;\r\n\r\n    const parts: Part[] = [];\r\n    if (typeof msg.content === \"string\") {\r\n      parts.push({ text: msg.content });\r\n    } else if (Array.isArray(msg.content)) {\r\n      for (const c of msg.content) {\r\n        if (c.type === \"text\" && c.text) {\r\n          parts.push({ text: c.text });\r\n        } else if (c.type === \"image_url\" && c.image_url?.url?.startsWith(\"data:\")) {\r\n          const [meta, base64] = c.image_url.url.split(\",\");\r\n          const mimeMatch = meta.match(/data:(.*?);base64/);\r\n          const mime = mimeMatch ? mimeMatch[1] : \"application/octet-stream\";\r\n          parts.push({ inlineData: { mimeType: mime, data: base64 } });\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n    geminiContents.push({ role: msg.role === \"user\" ? \"user\" : \"model\", parts });\r\n  }\r\n  return geminiContents;\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction createProxyForModel(vertexModelName: string) {\r\n  initializeVertexAIClient();\r\n\r\n  // Ensure the emulator/runtime injects the secret into the function process by\r\n  // declaring the secret in the onRequest options. This helps the emulator map\r\n  // .secret.local into process.env for this function.\r\n  return onRequest({ cors: true, secrets: [serviceAccountB64] }, async (request, response) => {\r\n    if (!vertex_ai) {\r\n      logger.error(\"Vertex AI client not initialized. Check project config and permissions.\");\r\n      response.status(500).send(\"Internal Server Error: AI client not initialized.\");\r\n      return;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    if (request.method !== \"POST\") {\r\n      response.status(405).send(\"Method Not Allowed\");\r\n      return;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    let openAIRequest: OpenAIRequest | undefined;\r\n    try {\r\n      openAIRequest = request.body;\r\n\r\n\r\n      if (!openAIRequest?.messages || !Array.isArray(openAIRequest.messages)) {\r\n        logger.error(\"Bad Request: Missing 'messages' array in request body.\");\r\n        response.status(400).send(\"Bad Request: Missing 'messages' array in request body.\");\r\n        return;\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      const systemMsg = openAIRequest.messages.find(m => m.role === \"system\");\r\n      const systemInstruction = systemMsg && typeof systemMsg.content === 'string'\r\n        ? { role: 'system', parts: [{ text: systemMsg.content }] }\r\n        : undefined;\r\n\r\n      const contents = mapMessagesToGemini(openAIRequest.messages);\r\n      logger.info(`[Transformation to Gemini] Model=${vertexModelName} Contents=${JSON.stringify(contents)}`);\r\n\r\n      const generativeModel: GenerativeModel = vertex_ai.getGenerativeModel({ model: vertexModelName, systemInstruction });\r\n      logger.info(`Forwarding translated request to Vertex AI model: ${vertexModelName} with STREAMING`);\r\n      \r\n      // Set up SSE headers for streaming\r\n      response.writeHead(200, {\r\n        'Content-Type': 'text/event-stream',\r\n        'Cache-Control': 'no-cache',\r\n        'Connection': 'keep-alive',\r\n      });\r\n\r\n      const timestamp = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\r\n      const completionId = `chatcmpl-${Date.now()}`;\r\n      \r\n      // Send initial empty choices with prompt filter results (Azure OpenAI format)\r\n      const initialChunk = {\r\n        choices: [],\r\n        created: 0,\r\n        id: \"\",\r\n        prompt_filter_results: [{\r\n          prompt_index: 0,\r\n          content_filter_results: {\r\n            hate: { filtered: false, severity: \"safe\" },\r\n            self_harm: { filtered: false, severity: \"safe\" },\r\n            sexual: { filtered: false, severity: \"safe\" },\r\n            violence: { filtered: false, severity: \"safe\" }\r\n          }\r\n        }]\r\n      };\r\n      response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(initialChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n\r\n      try {\r\n        // Use streaming API\r\n        logger.info('Calling generateContentStream on Vertex generativeModel', { model: vertexModelName });\r\n        const streamResult = await generativeModel.generateContentStream({ contents });\r\n        \r\n        let textBuffer = '';\r\n        let isFirstChunk = true;\r\n        let fullText = '';\r\n        let totalInputTokens = 0;\r\n        let totalOutputTokens = 0;\r\n\r\n        // Stream chunks as they arrive\r\n        for await (const chunk of streamResult.stream) {\r\n          const candidates = chunk.candidates;\r\n          if (!candidates || candidates.length === 0) {\r\n            continue;\r\n          }\r\n\r\n          const candidate = candidates[0];\r\n          const parts = candidate?.content?.parts || [];\r\n          \r\n          for (const part of parts) {\r\n            // Handle text content - but also check for embedded JSON function calls\r\n            if (part.text) {\r\n              let textContent = String(part.text);\r\n\r\n              // Log raw text content for debugging tool call detection\r\n              logger.debug('Processing Gemini text content chunk', {\r\n                textContent: textContent.slice(0, 200), // Log first 200 chars to avoid log spam\r\n                model: vertexModelName\r\n              });\r\n\r\n              // Write debug log to file for full visibility\r\n              try {\r\n                const debugLogDir = path.join(process.cwd(), 'logs', 'proxy_debug');\r\n                fs.mkdirSync(debugLogDir, { recursive: true });\r\n                const debugFilename = `gemini_debug_${vertexModelName}_${Date.now()}.txt`;\r\n                const debugPath = path.join(debugLogDir, debugFilename);\r\n                const debugContent = `[${new Date().toISOString()}] Processing chunk: ${textContent}\\n`;\r\n                fs.appendFileSync(debugPath, debugContent, { encoding: 'utf8' });\r\n              } catch (debugErr: any) {\r\n                logger.warn('Failed to write debug log to file', { err: debugErr?.message || debugErr });\r\n              }\r\n\r\n              // Check if Gemini is outputting function calls as JSON text instead of functionCall parts\r\n              // Look for JSON with \"tool_code\": specifically to avoid false positives\r\n              const toolCodeRegex = /\\{\\s*\"tool_code\"\\s*:\\s*\"([^\"]*)\"/g;\r\n\r\n              let toolCallsFound = false;\r\n              let processedTextContent = textContent;\r\n\r\n              // Check for tool_code JSON\r\n              let match;\r\n              while ((match = toolCodeRegex.exec(textContent)) !== null) {\r\n                try {\r\n                  // Extract the full JSON object containing tool_code\r\n                  const openBraceIndex = textContent.lastIndexOf('{', match.index);\r\n                  const closeBraceIndex = textContent.indexOf('}', match.index);\r\n toolCallData = JSON.parse(jsonCandidate);\r\n                    if (toolCallData && toolCallData.tool_code) {\r\n                      // Process the tool call\r\n                      const toolCode = toolCallData.tool_code;\r\n                      const funcMatch = toolCode.match(/^print\\(([^)]+)\\)$/);\r\n                      if (funcMatch) {\r\n                        const funcCall = funcMatch[1];\r\n                        const innerMatch = funcCall.match(/^([a-zA-Z_][a-zA-Z0-9_]*)\\((.*)\\)$/);\r\n                        if (innerMatch) {\r\n                          const funcName = innerMatch[1];\r\n                          const funcArgs = innerMatch[2].trim();\r\n\r\n                          // Parse arguments based on function name\r\n                          let argumentsObj: any = {};\r\n                          let shouldProcessToolCall = false;\r\n\r\n                          if (funcName === 'read_file' || funcName === 'list_files' || funcName === 'execute_command' || funcName === 'search_files' || funcName === 'list_code_definition_names') {\r\n                            // These functions expect string paths/args, parse them appropriately\r\n                            if (funcArgs.startsWith(\"'\") && funcArgs.endsWith(\"'\") || funcArgs.startsWith('\"') && funcArgs.endsWith('\"')) {\r\n                              const argValue = funcArgs.slice(1, -1);\r\n                              if (funcName === 'read_file') {\r\n                                argumentsObj = { path: argValue };\r\n                              } else if (funcName === 'list_files') {\r\n                                const recursiveMatch = argValue.match(/recursive\\s*=\\s*(true|false)/);\r\n                                argumentsObj = {\r\n                                  path: argValue.split(',', 1)[0].trim().slice(1, -1), // Extract path from first arg\r\n                                  recursive: recursiveMatch ? recursiveMatch[1] === 'true' : false\r\n                                };\r\n                              } else if (funcName === 'execute_command') {\r\n                                argumentsObj = { command: argValue };\r\n                              } else if (funcName === 'search_files') {\r\n                                const parts = argValue.split(',');\r\n                                argumentsObj = {\r\n                                  path: parts[0] ? parts[0].trim().slice(1, -1) : '',\r\n                                  regex: parts[1] ? parts[1].trim().slice(1, -1) : '',\r\n                                  file_pattern: parts[2] ? parts[2].trim().slice(1, -1) : undefined\r\n                                };\r\n                              } else if (funcName === 'list_code_definition_names') {\r\n                                argumentsObj = { path: argValue };\r\n                              }\r\n                            } else {\r\n                              // Fallback - treat as raw JSON\r\n                              try {\r\n                                argumentsObj = eval(`(${funcArgs})`);\r\n                              } catch {\r\n                                argumentsObj = { raw_args: funcArgs };\r\n                              }\r\n                            }\r\n                            shouldProcessToolCall = true;\r\n                          }\r\n\r\n                          if (shouldProcessToolCall) {\r\n                            logger.info('Detected tool call in JSON with tool_code, converting to OpenAI format', {\r\n                              toolCode,\r\n                              funcName,\r\n                              argumentsObj,\r\n                              originalJson: jsonCandidate\r\n                            });\r\n\r\n                            // Convert to OpenAI streaming tool call format\r\n                            const toolCallChunk: any = {\r\n                              choices: [{\r\n                                index: 0,\r\n                                delta: {\r\n                                  tool_calls: [{\r\n                                    index: 0,\r\n                                    id: `call_${Date.now()}`,\r\n                                    type: \"function\",\r\n                                    function: {\r\n                                      name: funcName,\r\n                                      arguments: JSON.stringify(argumentsObj)\r\n                                    }\r\n                                  }]\r\n                                },\r\n                                finish_reason: null\r\n                              }],\r\n                              created: timestamp,\r\n                              id: completionId,\r\n                              model: openAIRequest.model,\r\n                              object: \"chat.completion.chunk\"\r\n                            };\r\n\r\n                            response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(toolCallChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n                            processedTextContent = processedTextContent.replace(jsonCandidate, '').trim();\r\n                            toolCallsFound = true;\r\n                            isFirstChunk = false;\r\n                          }\r\n                        }\r\n                      }\r\n                    }\r\n                  }\r\n                } catch (jsonParseErr: any) {\r\n                  logger.warn('Failed to parse JSON containing tool_code', { error: jsonParseErr?.message || jsonParseErr, textSnippet: textContent.slice(match.index, match.index + 100) });\r\n                }\r\n              }\r\n\r\n              // Use the processed content (with tool calls removed) for text output\r\n              textContent = processedTextContent;\r\n\r\n              if (textContent) {\r\n                fullText += textContent;\r\n\r\n                const streamChunk: any = {\r\n                  choices: [{\r\n                    index: 0,\r\n                    delta: isFirstChunk\r\n                      ? { content: textContent, role: \"assistant\" }\r\n                      : { content: textContent },\r\n                    finish_reason: null\r\n                  }],\r\n                  created: timestamp,\r\n                  id: completionId,\r\n                  model: openAIRequest.model,\r\n                  object: \"chat.completion.chunk\"\r\n                };\r\n\r\n                response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(streamChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n                isFirstChunk = false;\r\n              }\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            // Handle Gemini function calls - convert to OpenAI streaming format for VS Code\r\n            if (part.functionCall) {\r\n              const functionCall = part.functionCall;\r\n              const functionName = functionCall.name;\r\n              const functionArgs = functionCall.args || {};\r\n\r\n              logger.info('Converting Gemini function call to OpenAI format', {\r\n                functionName,\r\n                args: functionArgs,\r\n                geminiFormat: JSON.stringify(functionCall)\r\n              });\r\n\r\n              // Convert to OpenAI streaming tool call format\r\n              // OpenAI uses delta.tool_calls array with function details\r\n              const toolCallChunk: any = {\r\n                choices: [{\r\n                  index: 0,\r\n                  delta: {\r\n                    tool_calls: [{\r\n                      index: 0,\r\n                      id: `call_${Date.now()}`,\r\n                      type: \"function\",\r\n                      function: {\r\n                        name: functionName,\r\n                        arguments: JSON.stringify(functionArgs)\r\n                      }\r\n                    }]\r\n                  },\r\n                  finish_reason: null\r\n                }],\r\n                created: timestamp,\r\n                id: completionId,\r\n                model: openAIRequest.model,\r\n                object: \"chat.completion.chunk\"\r\n              };\r\n\r\n              response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(toolCallChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n              isFirstChunk = false;\r\n            }\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        // Get the aggregated response for usage metadata\r\n        const aggregatedResponse = await streamResult.response;\r\n        if (aggregatedResponse?.usageMetadata) {\r\n          totalInputTokens = aggregatedResponse.usageMetadata.promptTokenCount || 0;\r\n          totalOutputTokens = aggregatedResponse.usageMetadata.candidatesTokenCount || 0;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        // Send final chunk with finish_reason\r\n        const finalChunk = {\r\n          choices: [{\r\n            index: 0,\r\n            delta: { content: null },\r\n            finish_reason: \"stop\"\r\n          }],\r\n          created: timestamp,\r\n          id: completionId,\r\n          model: openAIRequest.model,\r\n          object: \"chat.completion.chunk\"\r\n        };\r\n        response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(finalChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n\r\n        // Send usage chunk (empty choices array with usage stats)\r\n        const usageChunk = {\r\n          choices: [],\r\n          created: timestamp,\r\n          id: completionId,\r\n          model: openAIRequest.model,\r\n          object: \"chat.completion.chunk\",\r\n          usage: {\r\n            prompt_tokens: totalInputTokens,\r\n            completion_tokens: totalOutputTokens,\r\n            total_tokens: totalInputTokens + totalOutputTokens\r\n          }\r\n        };\r\n        response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(usageChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n\r\n        // Send [DONE] marker\r\n        response.write(`data: [DONE]\\n\\n`);\r\n        response.end();\r\n\r\n        logger.info(`[Streaming Complete] Model=${vertexModelName}, Tokens: ${totalInputTokens}+${totalOutputTokens}=${totalInputTokens + totalOutputTokens}`);\r\n        return;\r\n\r\n      } catch (vertexErr: any) {\r\n        logger.error('Vertex.generateContentStream  });\r\n        // Send error as SSE and close\r\n        const errorChunk = {\r\n          error: {\r\n            message: vertexErr?.message || 'Stream failed',\r\n            type: 'server_error'\r\n          }\r\n        };\r\n        response.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(errorChunk)}\\n\\n`);\r\n        response.end();\r\n        return;\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      // Old non-streaming code removed - everything below here is now unreachable\r\n      // but kept commented for reference if needed\r\n      /*\r\n      let result;\r\n      try {\r\n }\r\n\r\n  // Sort by arbitrage_score in descending order and take the top 3\r\n  const top3Keywords = scoredKeywords.sort((a, b) => b.arbitrage_score - a.arbitrage_score).slice(0, 3);\r\n\r\n  let html = `<ul style=\"margin-top: 5px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 20px;\">`;\r\n  top3Keywords.forEach((keywordData: any) => {\r\n    html += `<li><strong>“${keywordData.keyword}”</strong>: Search Volume: ${(keywordData.search_volume / 1000).toFixed(1)}k, Competition: ${keywordData.competition.toFixed(2)}</li>`;\r\n  });\r\n  html += `</ul>`;\r\n\r\n  return html;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Helper to generate HTML for Potential ROI\r\nfunction generatePotentialRoiHtml(topNClusters: any[], avgJobAmount: number): string {\r\n  if (!topNClusters || topNClusters.length === 0 || avgJobAmount === 0) {\r\n    return \"Potential ROI data not available.\";\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  const conversionRateAggressive = 0.10;\r\n  const ctrAggressive = 0.10;\r\n\r\n  // Find the fastest cluster and its ROI\r\n  let fastestCluster = topNClusters[0];\r\n  for (const cluster of topNClusters) {\r\n    if ((cluster.average_t_mid_base ?? 0) < (fastestCluster.average_t_mid_base ?? 0)) {\r\n      fastestCluster = cluster;\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  const fastestClusterRoi = (fastestCluster.aggregate_search_volume ?? 0) * ctrAggressive * conversionRateAggressive * avgJobAmount;\r\n  const minWeeks = Math.round(fastestCluster.average_t_mid_base ?? 0); // Add nullish coalescing\r\n\r\n  // Calculate total aggregate ROI for all top N clusters and find max weeks\r\n  let totalSearchVolumeAllClusters = 0;\r\n  let maxWeeks = 0;\r\n  topNClusters.forEach(cluster => {\r\n    totalSearchVolumeAllClusters += (cluster.aggregate_search_volume ?? 0);\r\n    if ((cluster.average_t_mid_base ?? 0) > maxWeeks) {\r\n      maxWeeks = (cluster.average_t_mid_base ?? 0);\r\n    }\r\n  });\r\n  maxWeeks = Math.round(maxWeeks);\r\n\r\n  const aggregateRoiAllClusters = totalSearchVolumeAllClusters * ctrAggressive * conversionRateAggressive * avgJobAmount;\r\n\r\n  return `We expect your ROI to be $${Math.round(fastestClusterRoi)} in the next ${minWeeks} weeks (based on your fastest-ranking cluster) and increase to $${Math.round(aggregateRoiAllClusters)} in the next ${maxWeeks} weeks (aggregating all top ${topNClusters.length} clusters).`;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Helper to generate HTML for Strategic Opportunity Prioritization (Hidden Gems)\r\nfunction generateStrategicOpportunityPrioritizationHtml(scoredKeywords: any[]): string {\r\n  if (!scoredKeywords || scoredKeywords.length === 0) {\r\n    return \"No strategic opportunities found.\";\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  // Filter for \"hidden gems\": high reward, moderate-to-high effort, medium-to-low velocity\r\n  // Arbitrage score > 20000 (example threshold for high reward)\r\n  // Competition between 0.3 and 0.7 (example threshold for moderate-to-high effort)\r\n  // Velocity < 10 (example threshold for medium-to-low velocity, meaning longer time to rank)\r\n  const hiddenGems = scoredKeywords.filter((k: any) =>\r\n    k.arbitrage_score > 20000 && k.competition >= 0.3 && k.competition <= 0.7 && (k.velocity ?? 0) < 10\r\n  ).sort((a, b) => b.arbitrage_score - a.arbitrage_score).slice(0, 3); // Sort by arbitrage_score and take top 3\r\n\r\n  if (hiddenGems.length === 0) {\r\n    return \"No hidden gems identified based on current criteria.\";\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  let html = `<p>Beyond immediate wins, these opportunities promise significant long-term rewards, balancing effort with substantial payoff:</p>`;\r\n  html += `<ul style=\"margin-top: 5px; list-style: disc; margin-left: 20px;\">`;\r\n  hiddenGems.forEach((keywordData: any) => {\r\n    html += `<li><strong>“${keywordData.keyword}”</strong>: Potential ROI: $${Math.round(keywordData.potential_roi)}, Time to Rank: ${Math.round(keywordData.time_to_rank)} weeks, Competition: ${keywordData.competition.toFixed(2)}</li>`;\r\n  });\r\n  html += `</ul>`;\r\n  html += `<p>These keywords, while potentially requiring more sustained effort, represent high-value targets for long-term market dominance.</p>`;\r\n\r\n  return html;\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Initialize Vertex AI outside the function for efficiency\r\nlet generativeModel: any;\r\n\r\nexport async function getGMBDataForPipeline(\r\n  pipeline: ContactPipeline\r\n): Promise<ContactPipeline> {\r\n  try {\r\n    // Log the service account being used by this function\r\n    try {\r\n      const metaUrl = \"http://metadata.google.internal/computeMetadata/v1/instance/service-accounts/default/email\";\r\n      const r = await fetch(metaUrl, { headers: { \"Metadata-Flavor\": \"Google\" } });\r\n      if (!r.ok) throw new Error(`Metadata server returned ${r.status}`);\r\n      const serviceAccountEmail = await r.text();\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getGMBDataForPipeline: Service Account Email: ${serviceAccountEmail}`);\r\n    } catch (metaErr: any) {\r\n      functions.logger.warn(`getGMBDataForPipeline: Could not retrieve service account email from metadata server: ${metaErr.message}`);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    const raw = pipeline.raw_data;\r\n\r\n    // const location = [raw.raw_contact?.city, raw.raw_contact?.state].filter(Boolean).join(\" \");\r\n      queries.push({label: \"business\", query: `${raw.business_name} ${location}`.trim()});\r\n      queries.push({label: \"competitors_zip\", query: `${raw.category} near ${raw.zip_code}`});\r\n    }\r\n    if (raw.category && (raw.raw_contact?.city || raw.raw_contact?.state)) {\r\n      const loc = [raw.raw_contact?.city, raw.raw_contact?.state].filter(Boolean).join(\" \");\r\n      queries.push({label: \"competitors_city\", query: `${raw.category} ${loc}`}); // Corrected query\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    functions.logger.info(\"getGMBDataForPipeline: Generated Serper queries:\", JSON.stringify(queries));\r\n    const serperQueries = queries.map(q => ({ q: q.query }));\r\n\r\n    const serperClient = new SerperClient();\r\n    const result = await serperClient.maps(serperQueries);\r\n\r\n    functions.logger.info(\"getGMBDataForPipeline: Serper API raw result:\", JSON.stringify(result, null, 2)); // Added pretty print for better readability\r\n\r\n    const gmbData: Record<\"business\" | \"competitors_zip\" | \"competitors_city\", any[]> = {\r\n      business: [],\r\n      competitors_zip: [],\r\n      competitors_city: [],\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    (result || []).forEach((res: any, index: number) => {\r\n      const originalQueryLabel = queries[index]?.label;\r\n      if (!originalQueryLabel) {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(`getGMBDataForPipeline: No query label for result index ${index}`);\r\n        return;\r\n      }\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getGMBDataForPipeline: Processing query label: ${originalQueryLabel}, result: ${JSON.stringify(res)}`);\r\n      if (res.places && Array.isArray(res.places)) {\r\n        res.places.forEach((place: any, placeIndex: number) => {\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getGMBDataForPipeline: Raw place data for ${originalQueryLabel} index ${placeIndex}: ${JSON.stringify(place)}`);\r\n          const mappedPlace = {\r\n            snippet_id: `${originalQueryLabel}_result_${placeIndex + 1}`,\r\n            business_name: place.title || null,\r\n            phone: place.phoneNumber || null,\r\n            website_url: place.website || null,\r\n            stars: place.rating || null,\r\n            number_of_reviews: place.reviews || place.ratingCount || null, // Added 'reviews' as an alternative for number_of_reviews\r\n            has_posts: false, // Not provided by Serper\r\n            detailed_metadata: {\r\n              address: place.address || null,\r\n              latitude: place.latitude || null,\r\n              longitude: place.longitude || null,\r\n              priceLevel: place.priceLevel || null,\r\n              type: place.type || null,\r\n              types: place.types || null,\r\n              description: place.description || null,\r\n              openingHours: place.openingHours || null,\r\n              thumbnailUrl: place.thumbnailUrl || null,\r\n              cid: place.cid || null,\r\n              fid: place.fid || null,\r\n              placeId: place.placeId || null,\r\n            },\r\n          };\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getGMBDataForPipeline: Mapped place for ${originalQueryLabel}: ${JSON.stringify(mappedPlace)}`);\r\n          gmbData[originalQueryLabel].push(mappedPlace);\r\n        });\r\n      }\r\n    });\r\n\r\n    pipeline.enriched_data = pipeline.enriched_data || {};\r\n    pipeline.enriched_data.gmb_data = functions.logger.error(\"getGMBDataForPipeline error\", {\r\n      message: errorMessage,\r\n      error: err,\r\n    });\r\n    pipeline.enriched_data = pipeline.enriched_data || {};\r\n    pipeline.enriched_data.gmb_data = {business: [], competitors_zip: [], competitors_city: []};\r\n    pipeline.error_message = err.message;\r\n    return pipeline;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nconst initializeVertexAI = async () => {\r\n  if (!generativeModel) {\r\n    // Use environment variables for configuration\r\n    const projectId = process.env.GCLOUD_PROJECT;\r\n    const location = 'us-central1'; // Or get from config if it varies\r\n    const vertex_ai = new VertexAI({ project: projectId, location: location });\r\n    generativeModel = vertex_ai.getGenerativeModel({ model: 'gemini-1.5-flash-001' }); // Using a more recent model\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n\r\n// Helper function to fetch news data from Firestore\r\nasync function fetchRealtimeNews(city: string, state: string): Promise<SafeRecord> {\r\n  const docId = `${city.toLowerCase().replace(/ /g, '')}${state.toLowerCase()}`;\r\n  const newsRef = db.collection(\"news_data\").doc(docId);\r\n\r\n  functions.logger.info(`fetchRealtimeNews: Attempting to retrieve news data for docId: ${docId}`);\r\n  try {\r\n    const newsSnapshot = await newsRef.get();\r\n    if (newsSnapshot.exists) {\r\n      const newsData = newsSnapshot.data();\r\n      functions.logger.info(`fetchRealtimeNews: Successfully retrieved news data for ${docId} from Firestore.`);\r\n      // Normalize: always return an object, not null/undefined\r\n      return (newsData?.data as SafeRecord) ?? {};\r\n    } else {\r\n      functions.logger.warn(`fetchRealtimeNews: News data for ${docId} not found in Firestore.`);\r\n      return {};\r\n    }\r\n  } catch (error: any) {\r\n    functions.logger.error(`fetchRealtimeNews: Error retrieving news data for ${docId} from Firestore: ${error.message}`, error);\r\n    return {};\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\n// New interfaces for chart requests\r\ninterface dataRequest {\r\n  requestId: string; // A unique ID for this specific chart request (frontend can use this to match response)\r\n  type: \"bar\" | \"line\" | \"pie_chart\" | \"seo_comparison\" | \"competitor_list\" | \"blog_benchmarks\" | \"funnel_chart\" | \"cluster_chart\" | \"top_keyword_opportunities_chart\" | \"arbitrage_opportunity_scatter_chart\"; // Updated types\r\n  city?: string; // Optional, for blog_benchmarks\r\n  category?: string; // Optional, for blog_benchmarks\r\n  title?: string; // Added for chart titles\r\n  data?: any; // Added for passing data directly for funnel/pie if needed, or for other chart types\r\n  innerRadius?: number; // Added for pie chart to make it a donut chart\r\n}\r\ninterface GetPageMetadataData {\r\n  pageId: string;\r\n  contactHash: string;\r\n  contentArray: Array<{ id: string; string: string }>;\r\n  dataRequest?: dataRequest[]; // New optional array to request charts\r\n  targetedBlob?: any; // New optional variable for targeted information\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Helper to get and deduplicate competitors from GMB data\r\nfunction getUniqueCompetitors(gmbData: SafeRecord): any[] {\r\n  const cityCompetitors = gmbData.competitors_city || [];\r\n  const zipCompetitors = gmbData.competitors_zip || [];\r\n  const allCompetitors = [...cityCompetitors, ...zipCompetitors];\r\n\r\n  // Simple deduplication by business_name, assuming it's unique enough for this context\r\n  return Array.from(new Map(allCompetitors.map((item: any) => [item.business_name, item])).values());\r\n}\r\n\r\n// Helper function to generate chart data based on request\r\nasync function generateChartData(dataObjects: any, request: dataRequest): Promise<any> {\r\n  const contact = dataObjects.contact;\r\n  const gmbData = dataObjects.gmbData || {}; // Ensure safe default\r\n  const arbitrageData = dataObjects.arbitrageData || {};\r\n\r\n  switch (request.type) {\r\n    case \"seo_comparison\":\r\n      // SEO Comparison Bar Chart: Populate with real data from gmbData\r\n      let actualTopCompetitorReviews = 0;\r\n      let actualCityAverageReviews = 0;\r\n      const uniqueCompetitorsForSeo = getUniqueCompetitors(gmbData);\r\n\r\n      if (uniqueCompetitorsForSeo.length > 0) {\r\n        functions.logger.info(\"All Competitors for SEO chart generation:\", JSON.stringify(uniqueCompetitorsForSeo));\r\n\r\n        if (uniqueCompetitorsForSeo.length > 0) {\r\n          // Find top competitor reviews\r\n          actualTopCompetitorReviews = Math.max(...uniqueCompetitorsForSeo.map((comp: any) => parseInt(comp.number_of_reviews) || 0));\r\n          functions.logger.info(\"Actual Top Competitor Reviews:\", actualTopCompetitorReviews);\r\n\r\n          // Calculate city average reviews\r\n          const totalReviews = uniqueCompetitorsForSeo.reduce((sum: number, comp: any) => sum + (parseInt(comp.number_of_reviews) || 0), 0);\r\n          actualCityAverageReviews = totalReviews / uniqueCompetitorsForSeo.length;\r\n          functions.logger.info(\"Actual City Average Reviews:\", actualCityAverageReviews);\r\n        } else {\r\n          functions.logger.warn(\"No competitors found in gmbData for chart generation.\");\r\n        }\r\n      } else {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(\"gmbData is null or undefined, cannot generate SEO comparison chart data.\");\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"bar\",\r\n        title: \"SEO Review Comparison\",\r\n        data: [\r\n          { label: contact?.business_name || \"Your Business\", value: contact?.review_count || 0 },\r\n          { label: \"Top Competitor\", value: actualTopCompetitorReviews },\r\n          { label: `${contact?.raw_contact?.city || \"City\"} Avg`, value: actualCityAverageReviews }\r\n        ]\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    case \"bar\":\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"bar\",\r\n        title: request.requestId, // Use requestId as title for generic charts\r\n        data: [\r\n          { label: \"Sample 1\", value: 10 },\r\n          { label: \"Sample 2\", value: 20 }\r\n        ]\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    case \"competitor_list\":\r\n      functions.logger.info(`generateChartData: Entering competitor_list case for requestId: ${request.requestId}`);\r\n      const competitors: any[] = [];\r\n      const uniqueCompetitors = getUniqueCompetitors(gmbData);\r\n      functions.logger.info(\"generateChartData: Unique Competitors for competitor list generation:\", JSON.stringify(uniqueCompetitors));\r\n\r\n      if (uniqueCompetitors.length > 0) {\r\n        if (uniqueCompetitors.length > 0) {\r\n          for (const comp of uniqueCompetitors) {\r\n            competitors.push({\r\n              business_name: comp.business_name || \"N/A\",\r\n              phone: comp.phoneNumber || comp.phone || \"N/A\", // Added phoneNumber as an alternative\r\n              website_url: comp.website || comp.website_url || \"N/A\", // Added website as an alternative\r\n              stars: parseFloat(comp.rating) || parseFloat(comp.stars) || 0, // Added rating as an alternative\r\n              number_of_reviews: parseInt(comp.reviews) || parseInt(comp.ratingCount) || parseInt(comp.number_of_reviews) || 0, // Added reviews and ratingCount as alternatives\r\n            });\r\n            functions.logger.info(`generateChartData: Mapped competitor: ${JSON.stringify(competitors[competitors.length - 1])}`);\r\n          }\r\n        } else {\r\n          functions.logger.warn(\"generateChartData: No unique competitors found in gmbData for competitor list generation.\");\r\n        }\r\n      } else {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(\"generateChartData: No GMB data available, cannot generate competitor list.\");\r\n      }\r\n      functions.logger.info(`generateChartData: Returning competitor_list for requestId: ${request.requestId}, data: ${JSON.stringify(competitors, null, 2)}`);\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"competitor_list\",\r\n        title: \"Local Competitors\",\r\n        data: competitors\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    case \"blog_benchmarks\":\r\n      const city = request.city || \"Denver\";\r\n      const category = request.category || \"Dental\";\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"blog_benchmarks\",\r\n        title: `Blog Benchmarks for ${city} ${category}`,\r\n        data: {\r\n          city: city,\r\n          category: category,\r\n          smbAvgBlogsPerMonth: 8,\r\n          industryAvgBlogsPerMonth: 12,\r\n          recommendedBlogsPerMonth: 4,\r\n          seoImpactPercent: 18\r\n        }\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    case \"arbitrage_opportunity_scatter_chart\":\r\n      const scoredKeywords = arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.scored_keywords || [];\r\n      const allBandedClusters = arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters || {};\r\n\r\n      const top4ClusterKeywordsSet = new Set(getScoredKeywordsForTopNClusters(scoredKeywords, allBandedClusters, 4).map((k: any) => k.keyword));\r\n\r\n      const scatterData = scoredKeywords.map((k: any) => {\r\n        const timeToRankWeeks = k.t_mid_base; // Directly use t_mid_base\r\n        const potentialRevenue = k.potential_roi; // Using potential_roi as revenue\r\n        const isTop4Cluster = top4ClusterKeywordsSet.has(k.keyword);\r\n\r\n        let category = \"Long-Term\";\r\n        let color = \"#FF6384\"; // Red\r\n        let size = 10;\r\n\r\n        if (timeToRankWeeks <= 12) { // Short-term: <= 12 weeks\r\n          category = \"Short-Term\";\r\n          color = \"#36A2EB\"; // Blue\r\n          size = 15; // Emphasize short-term wins\r\n        } else if (timeToRankWeeks <= 52) { // Medium-term: <= 52 weeks\r\n          category = \"Medium-Term\";\r\n          color = \"#FFCE56\"; // Yellow\r\n          size = 12;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        // Override color and size if it's a top 4 cluster keyword\r\n        if (isTop4Cluster) {\r\n          category = \"Top 4 Cluster\"; // Assign a new category for legend\r\n          color = \"#4CAF50\"; // Vibrant Green for top 4\r\n          size = 20; // Significantly larger size\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        return {\r\n          x: timeToRankWeeks // Time to Rank on X-axis\r\n          , y: potentialRevenue // Revenue on Y-axis\r\n          , keyword: k.keyword\r\n          , search_volume: k.search_volume\r\n          , velocity: k.velocity\r\n          , competition: k.competition\r\n          , arbitrage_score: k.arbitrage_score\r\n          , category: category\r\n          , color: color\r\n          , size: size\r\n          , isTop4Cluster: isTop4Cluster // Include the flag for frontend reference\r\n        };\r\n      });\r\n\r\n      // Calculate dynamic Y-axis max\r\n      const maxRevenue = scatterData.reduce((max: number, point: any) => Math.max(max, point.y), 0);\r\n      const yAxisMaxWithPadding = maxRevenue * 1.20; // 20% padding at the top\r\n\r\n      // Determine X-axis max dynamically based on the maximum timeToRankWeeks plus a buffer\r\n      const maxX = scatterData.reduce((max: number, point: any) => Math.max(max, point.x), 0);\r\n      const xAxisMaxWithPadding = maxX > 0 ? maxX * 1.20 : 10; // 20% padding, or a default if no data\r\n\r\n      // Calculate min and max weeks from ALL scored keywords for secondXAxisGridLine\r\n      const allTimesToRank = scoredKeywords.map((k: any) => k.t_mid_base);\r\n      const minOverallWeeks = allTimesToRank.length > 0 ? Math.min(...allTimesToRank) : 0;\r\n      const maxOverallWeeks = allTimesToRank.length > 0 ? Math.max(...allTimesToRank) : 0;\r\n      const midpointOverallWeeks = (minOverallWeeks + maxOverallWeeks) / 2;\r\n      const secondXAxisGridLine = Math.round(Math.min(24, midpointOverallWeeks)); // Lesser of 6 months (24 weeks) or midpoint\r\n\r\n      // Calculate second Y-axis grid line (lowest revenue of top 4 cluster keywords with buffer)\r\n      const top4ClusterKeywordsForYAxis = getScoredKeywordsForTopNClusters(scoredKeywords, allBandedClusters, 4);\r\n      let secondYAxisGridLine = 0;\r\n      if (top4ClusterKeywordsForYAxis.length > 0) {\r\n        const minRevenueOfTop4 = Math.min(...top4ClusterKeywordsForYAxis.map((k: any) => k.potential_roi));\r\n        secondYAxisGridLine = Math.round(minRevenueOfTop4 * 0.95); // 5% buffer below\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"scatter\",\r\n        title: \"Arbitrage Opportunity Landscape\",\r\n        data: scatterData,\r\n        xAxisLabel: \"Time to Rank (Weeks)\",\r\n        yAxisLabel: \"Potential Revenue ($)\",\r\n        categories: [\"Short-Term\", \"Medium-Term\", \"Long-Term\", \"Top 4 Cluster\"], // Added new category\r\n        xAxisMin: 0,\r\n        xAxisMax: xAxisMaxWithPadding,\r\n        yAxisMin: 0,\r\n        yAxisMax: yAxisMaxWithPadding,\r\n        secondXAxisGridLine: secondXAxisGridLine,\r\n        secondYAxisGridLine: secondYAxisGridLine,\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    case \"pie_chart\":\r\n      const leadSerpPie = dataObjects.lead_serp;\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"pie_chart\",\r\n        title: request.title || \"Keyword Search Volume Distribution\",\r\n        data: [\r\n          { category: \"Long Distance Movers\", value: leadSerpPie.cluster_long_distance_search_volume },\r\n          { category: \"Residential Movers\", value: leadSerpPie.cluster_residential_search_volume },\r\n          { category: \"Office/Commercial Movers\", value: leadSerpPie.cluster_office_commercial_search_volume },\r\n          { category: \"Other Keywords\", value: leadSerpPie.cluster_other_search_volume }\r\n        ],\r\n        innerRadius: request.innerRadius || 0\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    case \"top_keyword_opportunities_chart\":\r\n      const topKeywords = arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.scored_keywords\r\n        .slice(0, 5) // Get top 5 keywords\r\n        .map((k: any) => ({\r\n          category: k.keyword,\r\n          value: k.arbitrage_score // Use arbitrage_score as the value\r\n        }));\r\n      return {\r\n        requestId: request.requestId,\r\n        type: \"bar\",\r\n        title: request.title || \"Top Keyword Opportunities by Arbitrage Score\",\r\n        data: topKeywords\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    default:\r\n      functions.logger.warn(`generateChartData: Unknown chart type requested: ${request.type}`);\r\n      return { requestId: request.requestId, error: `Unknown chart type: ${request.type}` };\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\nexport const getPageMetadata = functions.https.onCall(\r\n  async (request, context) => {\r\n    functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata called with request data:\", JSON.stringify(request.data, null, 2)); // Added JSON.stringify for full content\r\n\r\n    const { pageId, contactHash, contentArray, dataRequest, targetedBlob } = request.data as GetPageMetadataData;\r\n    functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: dataRequest content at start: ${JSON.stringify(dataRequest, null, 2)}`);\r\n\r\n    if (!pageId || !contactHash || !contentArray || !Array.isArray(contentArray)) {\r\n      throw new functions.https.HttpsError(\r\n        \"invalid-argument\",\r\n        \"The function must be called with pageId, contactHash, and contentArray.\"\r\n      );\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    await initializeVertexAI();\r\n\r\n    let contactData: RawContact | null = null;\r\n    let contactDocId: string | null = null; // Declare contactDocId here\r\n    let weatherData: SafeRecord = {};\r\n    let newsData: SafeRecord = {};\r\n    let dataUsaKeyPointsData: SafeRecord = {};\r\n    let marketingStrategyData: SafeRecord = {};\r\n    let gmbData: SafeRecord = {};\r\n    let averageOrderValues: SafeRecord = {};\r\n    let annualRevenueGain = 0; // Initialize annualRevenueGain\r\n    let arbitrageData: SafeRecord = {}; // Initialize arbitrageData\r\n    let avgJobAmount: number = 0; // Initialize avgJobAmount\r\n\r\n    functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata: Starting function execution.\");\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n      // 1. Retrieve contact object using contactHash\r\n      const contactSnapshot = await db.collection(\"contacts\").where(\"hash\", \"==\", contactHash).limit(1).get();\r\n      if (contactSnapshot.empty) {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(`getPageMetadata: Contact with hash ${contactHash} not found. Proceeding without contact-specific data.`);\r\n        // Set contactData to null and continue execution\r\n        contactData = null;\r\n      } else {\r\n        contactData = contactSnapshot.docs[0].data() as RawContact;\r\n        contactDocId = contactSnapshot.docs[0].id; // Assign contactDocId here\r\n        functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata: Contact data retrieved:\", JSON.stringify(contactData));\r\n        functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata: Contact enriched_data (full content):\", JSON.stringify(contactData.enriched_data));\r\n\r\n        // NEW LOGIC START: Check if gmb_data is missing or empty and trigger a fresh request\r\n        const currentGmbData = (contactData.enriched_data?.gmb_data as SafeRecord) ?? {};\r\n        const hasGmbData = currentGmbData.business?.length > 0 || currentGmbData.competitors_zip?.length > 0 || currentGmbData.competitors_city?.length > 0;\r\n\r\n        if (!hasGmbData && contactData.raw_contact && contactData.category) {\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: gmb_data is empty or missing for contact ${contactHash}. Initiating fresh GMB data request.`);\r\n          const pipelineForGMB: ContactPipeline = {\r\n            raw_data: contactData, // Pass the entire RawContact document\r\n            enriched_data: contactData.enriched_data || {}, // Ensure enriched_data is an object\r\n            error_message: contactData.error_message,\r\n            email: contactData.email || null, // Add email\r\n            phone: contactData.phone || null, // Add phone\r\n            status: contactData.status || \"pending\", // Add status, default to \"pending\"\r\n            contact_id: contactDocId!, // Add contact_id\r\n          };\r\n          const updatedPipeline = await getGMBDataForPipeline(pipelineForGMB);\r\n\r\n          // Update contactData with the newly fetched GMB data\r\n          contactData.enriched_data = updatedPipeline.enriched_data;\r\n          contactData.error_message = updatedPipeline.error_message;\r\n\r\n          // Persist the updated contactData back to Firestore\r\n          if (contactDocId) {\r\n            await db.collection(\"contacts\").doc(contactDocId).update({\r\n              enriched_data: contactData.enriched_data,\r\n              error_message: contactData.error_message,\r\n            });\r\n            functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Updated contact ${contactDocId} in Firestore with new GMB data.`);\r\n          }\r\n        } else if (hasGmbData) {\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Existing gmb_data found for contact ${contactHash}. Skipping fresh request.`);\r\n        } else {\r\n          functions.logger.warn(`getPageMetadata: Cannot initiate fresh GMB data request for contact ${contactHash} due to missing raw_contact or category.`);\r\n        }\r\n        // NEW LOGIC END\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata: Before arbitrage data retrieval logic.\");\r\n      // 2. Fetch arbitrage data from Firestore\r\n      if (contactData?.raw_contact?.city && contactData?.raw_contact?.state && contactData?.category) {\r\n        const city = contactData.raw_contact.city.toLowerCase().replace(/ /g, '-');\r\n        const state = contactData.raw_contact.state.toLowerCase();\r\n\r\n        // Prioritize raw_contact.category for path construction, fallback to contactData.category\r\n        const rawCategoryFromContact = contactData.category;\r\n        functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Raw category from contactData.raw_contact.category (or fallback): ${rawCategoryFromContact}`);\r\n\r\n        // Sanitize category to ensure it's a valid Firestore document ID segment\r\n        let sanitizedCategory = rawCategoryFromContact;\r\n        if (sanitizedCategory) {\r\n          sanitizedCategory = sanitizedCategory.replace(/[^a-zA-Z0-9-_]/g, '').toLowerCase();\r\n        } else {\r\n          sanitizedCategory = \"unknown-category\"; // Fallback if category is null/undefined\r\n        }\r\n        functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Sanitized category for path: ${sanitizedCategory}`);\r\n\r\n        const path = `dataUsaKeyPoints/${city}-${state}/serp/arbitrage-lite/${sanitizedCategory}/data`;\r\n        functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata: Constructed Firestore doc path:\", path);\r\n\r\n        const docRef = db.doc(path);\r\n        functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Attempting to retrieve arbitrage data from const path: ${docRef.path}`);\r\n        const arbitrageSnapshot = await docRef.get();\r\n        if (arbitrageSnapshot.exists) {\r\n          const fetchedFullArbitrageDocument = arbitrageSnapshot.data() ?? {}; // Store the full document\r\n          arbitrageData = fetchedFullArbitrageDocument; // Assign the full document to arbitrageData\r\n          avgJobAmount = fetchedFullArbitrageDocument.avgJobAmount ?? 0; // Extract top-level avgJobAmount\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Successfully retrieved arbitrage data from ${docRef.path} from Firestore.`);\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Full Arbitrage Document Content: ${JSON.stringify(arbitrageData, null, 2)}`);\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Extracted avgJobAmount: ${avgJobAmount}`);\r\n        } else {\r\n          functions.logger.warn(`getPageMetadata: Arbitrage data for ${docRef.path} not found in Firestore.`);\r\n          arbitrageData = {};\r\n          avgJobAmount = 0;\r\n        }\r\n      } else {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(\"getPageMetadata: City, state, or category is not available for arbitrage data enrichment.\");\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      functions.logger.info(\"getPageMetadata: After arbitrage data retrieval logic.\");\r\n\r\n      // 3. Fetch weather data from Firestore\r\n      if (contactData?.raw_contact?.city && contactData?.raw_contact?.state) {\r\n        const city = contactData.raw_contact.city;\r\n        const state = contactData.raw_contact.state;\r\n        const normalizedCityState = normalizeCityState(city, state);\r\n        functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Attempting to retrieve weather data for ${city}, ${state}`);\r\n\r\n        const weatherRef = db.collection(\"dataUsaKeyPoints\").doc(normalizedCityState).collection(\"weather\").doc(\"latest\");\r\n        try {\r\n          const weatherSnapshot = await weatherRef.get();\r\n          if (weatherSnapshot.exists) {\r\n            const cachedWeather = weatherSnapshot.data();\r\n            weatherData = (cachedWeather?.data as SafeRecord) ?? {};\r\n            functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Successfully retrieved weather data for ${normalizedCityState} from Firestore.`);\r\n          } else {\r\n            functions.logger.warn(`getPageMetadata: Weather data for ${normalizedCityState} not found in Firestore.`);\r\n            weatherData = {};\r\n          }\r\n        } catch (error: any) {\r\n          functions.logger.error(`getPageMetadata: Error retrieving weather data for ${normalizedCityState} from Firestore: ${error.message}`, error);\r\n          weatherData = {};\r\n        }\r\n      } else {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(\"getPageMetadata: City or state is not available for weather enrichment.\");\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      // 4. Fetch real-time news data\r\n      if (contactData?.raw_contact?.city && contactData?.raw_contact?.state) {\r\n        const fetchedNews = await fetchRealtimeNews(contactData.raw_contact.city, contactData.raw_contact.state);\r\n        newsData = fetchedNews ?? {};\r\n        functions.logger.info(\"News data fetched:\", newsData);\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      // 5. Fetch DataUSA Key Points data and Average Order Values\r\n      if (contactData?.raw_contact?.city && contactData?.raw_contact?.state) {\r\n        const city = contactData.raw_contact.city.toLowerCase().replace(/ /g, '-');\r\n        const state = contactData.raw_contact.state.toLowerCase();\r\n        const docId = `${city}-${state}`; // Use city-state format\r\n        functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Attempting to retrieve DataUSA key points for docId: ${docId}`);\r\n        const cityDataSnapshot = await db.collection(\"dataUsaKeyPoints\").doc(docId).get(); // Using dataUsaKeyPoints as the consolidated collection\r\n        if (cityDataSnapshot.exists) {\r\n          const cityData = cityDataSnapshot.data();\r\n          dataUsaKeyPointsData = (cityData as SafeRecord) ?? {};\r\n          averageOrderValues = (cityData?.averageOrderValues as SafeRecord) ?? {};\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: City data for ${docId} retrieved:`, cityData);\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Average Order Values for ${docId}:`, averageOrderValues);\r\n        } else {\r\n          functions.logger.warn(`getPageMetadata: City data for ${docId} not found. Skipping enrichment.`);\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      // 6. Fetch Marketing Strategy data\r\n      const marketingStrategySnapshot = await db.collection(\"marketingStrategy\").doc(\"main-strategy\").get();\r\n      if (marketingStrategySnapshot.exists) {\r\n        marketingStrategyData = marketingStrategySnapshot.data() ?? {};\r\n        functions.logger.info(\"Marketing Strategy data retrieved:\", marketingStrategyData);\r\n      } else {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(\"Marketing Strategy data not found. Skipping enrichment.\");\r\n        marketingStrategyData = {};\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      gmbData = (contactData?.enriched_data?.gmb_data as SafeRecord) ?? {}; // This line will now reflect the potentially updated gmbData\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: gmbData after assignment from contactData.enriched_data: ${JSON.stringify(gmbData, null, 2)}`);\r\n\r\n      // Calculate Annual Revenue Gain using arbitrageData.arbitrageData.avgJobAmount\r\n      if (avgJobAmount > 0) {\r\n        annualRevenueGain = 10 * avgJobAmount * 12; // 10 new clients/month * avg job amount * 12 months\r\n        functions.logger.info(`Calculated Annual Revenue Gain using avgJobAmount: $${annualRevenueGain}`);\r\n      } else {\r\n        functions.logger.warn(\"Missing or invalid avgJobAmount for annual revenue gain calculation.\");\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: arbitrageData before llmInputObjects creation: ${JSON.stringify(arbitrageData, null, 2)}`);\r\n\r\n      // Dynamically get the first 4 clusters for ROI calculation and pie chart (moved outside llmInputObjects)\r\n      const top4ClustersRaw = getFirstNClusters(arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters || {}, 4);\r\n\r\n      const top4ClustersForLlm = top4ClustersRaw.map(cluster => ({\r\n        primary: cluster.primary,\r\n        related: cluster.related,\r\n        aggregate_search_volume: cluster.aggregate_search_volume,\r\n        average_competition: cluster.average_competition,\r\n        average_velocity: cluster.average_velocity,\r\n        average_cpc: cluster.average_cpc,\r\n        average_t_mid_base: cluster.average_t_mid_base, // Explicitly include this\r\n        base_value_score: cluster.base_value_score, // Also include this as it's part of the new structure\r\n        value_score: cluster.value_score,\r\n        long_term_arbitrage_score_cluster: cluster.long_term_arbitrage_score_cluster,\r\n        llm_content_ideas: cluster.llm_content_ideas,\r\n        cluster_keywords_details: cluster.cluster_keywords_details, // Include this for getScoredKeywordsForTopNClusters\r\n      }));\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: top4ClustersForLlm before llmInputObjects: ${JSON.stringify(top4ClustersForLlm, null, 2)}`);\r\n\r\n      // 8. Prepare LLM input\r\n      const llmInputObjects = {\r\n        contact: contactData,\r\n        weather: weatherData,\r\n        news: newsData,\r\n        dataUsaKeyPoints: dataUsaKeyPointsData,\r\n        marketingStrategy: marketingStrategyData,\r\n        gmbData: gmbData, // Include gmbData for LLM to use in contentArray\r\n        annualRevenueGain: annualRevenueGain, // Include annualRevenueGain for LLM\r\n        targetedBlob: targetedBlob, // Include targetedBlob for LLM\r\n        arbitrageData: arbitrageData.arbitrageData, // Pass the nested arbitrageData to LLM\r\n        avgJobAmount: avgJobAmount, // Use the correctly extracted top-level avgJobAmount\r\n        lead_serp: { // New object to hold calculated arbitrage data for LLM\r\n          estimated_revenue_range: calculateEstimatedRevenueRange(\r\n            arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters ? calculateTotalSearchVolume(arbitrageData.arbitrageData.all_banded_clusters) : 0,\r\n            0.05, 0.10, 1000, 2000, 0.05, 0.10 // Conservative/Aggressive Conversion Rate, Avg Customer Value, CTR\r\n          ),\r\n          // Ensure all_banded_clusters is always an object for calculateTotalSearchVolume\r\n          total_search_volume: calculateTotalSearchVolume(arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters || {}), // Ensure this is correctly calculated\r\n          total_keywords_in_pool: arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.total_keywords_in_pool || 0,\r\n          visit_projection_range: calculateVisitProjectionRange(\r\n            arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters ? calculateTotalSearchVolume(arbitrageData.arbitrageData.all_banded_clusters) : 0,\r\n            0.05, 0.10 // Conservative/Aggressive CTR\r\n          ),\r\n          // Dynamically get the first 4 clusters for ROI calculation and pie chart\r\n          top_4_clusters: top4ClustersForLlm,\r\n          agr_top_4_roi: calculateAgrRoiForClusters(\r\n            top4ClustersForLlm,\r\n            0.05, 0.10, 1000, 2000, 0.05, 0.10 // Conservative/Aggressive Conversion Rate, Avg Customer Value, CTR\r\n          ),\r\n          scored_keywords: (arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.scored_keywords || [])\r\n            .map((k: any) => ({\r\n              ...k,\r\n              time_to_rank: k.t_mid_base ?? 0 // Use t_mid_base directly for Time_to_Rank with fallback\r\n            })),\r\n          customer_domain_authority: arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.customer_domain_authority || {},\r\n          estimated_conversions_aggressive: Math.round(\r\n            (arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters ? calculateTotalSearchVolume(arbitrageData.arbitrageData.all_banded_clusters) : 0) * 0.10 * 0.10\r\n          ),\r\n          // Use dynamically selected clusters for pie chart categories\r\n          cluster_long_distance_search_volume: top4ClustersForLlm[0]?.aggregate_search_volume ?? 0,\r\n          cluster_residential_search_volume: top4ClustersForLlm[1]?.aggregate_search_volume ?? 0,\r\n          cluster_office_commercial_search_volume: top4ClustersForLlm[2]?.aggregate_search_volume ?? 0,\r\n          cluster_other_search_volume: (arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters ? calculateTotalSearchVolume(arbitrageData.arbitrageData.all_banded_clusters) : 0) -\r\n                                       (top4ClustersForLlm.reduce((sum: number, cluster: any) => sum + (cluster.aggregate_search_volume ?? 0), 0)),\r\n          high_value_keywords_summary_html: generateTopArbitrageOpportunitiesHtml(getScoredKeywordsForTopNClusters(arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.scored_keywords || [], arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters || {}, 4)),\r\n          potential_roi_summary_html: generatePotentialRoiHtml(top4ClustersForLlm, avgJobAmount),\r\n          hidden_gems_summary_html: generateKeywordSummaryHtml(\r\n            getScoredKeywordsForTopNClusters(arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.scored_keywords || [], arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters || {}, 4)\r\n              .filter((k: any) => k.normalized_arbitrage_score >= 1 && k.normalized_arbitrage_score <= 10 && k.velocity > 10 && k.competition < 0.5).slice(0, 2) || [], // Example criteria for hidden gems\r\n            \"Hidden Gems\"\r\n          ),\r\n          strategic_opportunity_prioritization_html: generateStrategicOpportunityPrioritizationHtml(getScoredKeywordsForTopNClusters(arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.scored_keywords || [], arbitrageData.arbitrageData?.all_banded_clusters || {}, 4)), // New section\r\n        }\r\n      };\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: llmInputObjects.lead_serp content: ${JSON.stringify(llmInputObjects.lead_serp, null, 2)}`);\r\n\r\n      const PROMPT = `\r\n        You are a data resolver and content cleaner. Your primary task is to replace variables in the provided strings with values from the given data objects, apply fallbacks, and ensure the resulting sentences are grammatically correct and human-readable.\r\n\r\n        Additionally, where possible, enhance the tone of the resolved sentences to be warmer, more personal, and foster a stronger connection with the reader. The goal is to make the content feel like a one-to-one communication, even if the original sentence is generic.\r\n\r\n        CRITICAL: Your response MUST be a single, valid JSON array. All string values within the JSON MUST be properly escaped. Do NOT include any additional text or formatting outside of the JSON array.\r\n\r\n        **Input Data:**\r\n        - \\`contact\\`: A JSON object containing contact details.\r\n        - \\`weather\\`: A JSON object containing real-time weather data.\r\n        - \\`news\\`: A JSON object containing real-time news data.\r\n        - \\`dataUsaKeyPoints\\`: A JSON object containing demographic and economic data for a specific city/state.\r\n        - \\`marketingStrategy\\`: A JSON object containing comprehensive marketing research analysis.\r\n        - \\`gmbData\\`: A JSON object containing Google My Business data, including competitor information.\r\n        - \\`annualRevenueGain\\`: A number representing the calculated annual revenue gain.\r\n        - \\`targetedBlob\\`: A JSON object containing specific targeted information (e.g., SEO, email).\r\n        - \\`arbitrageData\\`: A JSON object containing SEO arbitrage data.\r\n        - \\`contentArray\\`: An array of objects, each with an \\`id\\` and a \\`string\\` that may contain variables.\r\n\r\n        **Variable Format:**\r\n        Variables are enclosed in double curly braces and are prefixed with the object name, followed by a dot, and then the property name (e.g., \\`{{contact.firstName}}\\`, \\`{{weather.temperature}}\\`, \\`{{news.general[0].title}}\\`, \\`{{dataUsaKeyPoints.data.demographics.2023 population}}\\`, \\`{{marketingStrategy.strategydata.executive summary}}\\`, \\`{{gmbData.business[0].business_name}}\\`, \\`{{annualRevenueGain}}\\`, \\`{{targeted_blob.seo}}\\`, \\`{{targeted_blob.email}}\\`, \\`{{arbitrageData.total_keywords_in_pool}}\\`).\r\n\r\n        **Tasks:**\r\n        1.  **Variable Replacement:** For each string in \\`contentArray\\`, replace all occurrences of variables with their corresponding values from the \\`contact\\`, \\`weather\\`, \\`news\\`, \\`dataUsaKeyPoints\\`, \\`marketingStrategy\\`, \\`gmbData\\`, \\`annualRevenueGain\\`, \\`targetedBlob\\`, and \\`arbitrageData\\` objects.\r\n            *   If a variable's value is null, undefined, or the path does not exist, generate a contextually appropriate fallback. For example, if \\`{{contact.firstName}}\\` is missing, use \"there\" or \"our valued customer\". If a numerical value like temperature is missing, use \"the local area\" or \"the region\".\r\n            *   For array variables (e.g., \\`{{news.general[0].title}}\\`), ensure you handle array indexing correctly. If the index is out of bounds, provide a suitable fallback.\r\n            *   When \\`targetedBlob\\` variables are present (e.g., \\`{{targeted_blob.seo}}\\`), generate 2-3 sentences explaining how the agent can improve the business in that specific area (e.g., SEO, email marketing) based on the provided \\`targetedBlob\\` content.\r\n        3.  **Grammar and Punctuation Cleanup:** After variable replacement, review each resulting sentence. Correct any grammatical errors, awkward phrasing, or punctuation issues to ensure the output is natural, fluent, and human-readable.\r\n        3.  **Output Format:** Return a JSON array where each object corresponds to an input string from \\`contentArray\\`. Each object must have:\r\n            *   \\`id\\`: The original \\`id\\` from the input \\`contentArray\\`.\r\n            *   \\`resolvedString\\`: The final, processed string after variable replacement and cleanup. This string MUST be a valid JSON string (i.e., all internal quotes and special characters must be properly escaped).\r\n\r\n        **Checklist before returning data:**\r\n        - [ ] The response is a single, valid JSON array.\r\n        - [ ] All string values within the JSON are properly escaped.\r\n        - [ ] No additional text or formatting is included outside of the JSON array.\r\n        - [ ] All variables are correctly replaced, with appropriate fallbacks for missing data.\r\n        - [ ] The resolved strings are grammatically correct and human-readable.\r\n        - [ ] For \\`targetedBlob\\` variables, 2-3 sentences on business improvement are generated.\r\n\r\n        Now, process the following:\r\n\r\n        **Data Objects:**\r\n        ${JSON.stringify(llmInputObjects, null, 2)}\r\n\r\n        **Strings to Resolve:**\r\n        ${JSON.stringify(contentArray, null, 2)}\r\n\r\n        Your JSON Array Response:\r\n      `;\r\n\r\n      const result = await generativeModel.generateContent({\r\n        contents: [{ role: \"user\", parts: [{ text: PROMPT }] }],\r\n      });\r\n\r\n      const response = result.response;\r\n      const text = response?.candidates?.[0]?.content?.parts?.[0]?.text || \"\";\r\n      const cleaned = text.replace(/```json\\s*|```\\s*$/g, \"\").trim();\r\n\r\n      let resolvedContent: Array<{ id: string; resolvedString: string }> = [];\r\n      try {\r\n        resolvedContent = JSON.parse(cleaned);\r\n        // Post-process resolvedString to ensure it's valid JSON string (escaped)\r\n        resolvedContent = resolvedContent.map(item => ({\r\n          id: item.id,\r\n          resolvedString: item.resolvedString // Directly use the resolved string from LLM\r\n        }));\r\n      } catch (e: any) {\r\n        functions.logger.error(`getPageMetadata: JSON parse error from LLM: ${e.message}`);\r\n        // Fallback if LLM returns invalid JSON\r\n        resolvedContent = contentArray.map(item => ({\r\n          id: item.id,\r\n          resolvedString: `Error resolving string for ID ${item.id}. Original: \"${item.string}\"`\r\n        }));\r\n      }\r\n\r\n      const generatedData: any[] = [];\r\n      if (dataRequest && Array.isArray(dataRequest)) {\r\n        functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Processing dataRequest array with ${dataRequest.length} items.`);\r\n        for (const dataReq of dataRequest) {\r\n          functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Calling generateChartData for requestId: ${dataReq.requestId}, type: ${dataReq.type}`);\r\n          try {\r\n            const chartData = await generateChartData(llmInputObjects, dataReq);\r\n            functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Generated chart data for ${dataReq.requestId}: ${JSON.stringify(chartData, null, 2)}`);\r\n            generatedData.push(chartData);\r\n          } catch (chartError: any) {\r\n            functions.logger.error(`Error generating chart ${dataReq.requestId}:`, chartError);\r\n            generatedData.push({ requestId: dataReq.requestId, error: chartError.message });\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n      functions.logger.info(`getPageMetadata: Final generatedData array: ${JSON.stringify(generatedData, null, 2)}`);\r\n\r\n      return {\r\n        pageId: pageId,\r\n        content: resolvedContent,\r\n        data: generatedData,\r\n      };\r\n\r\n    } catch (error: any) {\r\n      functions.logger.error(\"Error in getPageMetadata:\", error); // Changed to log the full error object\r\n      throw new functions.https.HttpsError(\"internal\", \"Unable to process request.\", error.message);\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n);\r\n\n```",
